```

This CSS code will apply a font size of 20px to all elements within the body tag of your HTML document. You can adjust the value to other pixel sizes as needed.

Here are some additional options:

* To apply the font size to a specific element or class, replace `body` with the desired element or class selector.
* To set the font size for specific headings, you can use the following tags:

```css
h1 {
  font-size: 28px;
}

h2 {
  font-size: 24px;
}

h3 {
  font-size: 20px;
}

h4 {
  font-size: 18px;
}

h5 {
  font-size: 16px;
}

h6 {
  font-size: 14px;
}
```

Remember to adjust the font size values according to your design preferences and the overall hierarchy of your web page.
